<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101948740129440></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101948740129440><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101948740129440>RE: Strength</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101948740129440#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=140616><span id=Guru>Victorex</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>52 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 22nd 11:03 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Strength does 3 things.<br><br>1) Add to your MAXIMUM damage.<br>2) Increase your ATK number.<br>3) Allow you to carry more. <br><br>Let's look at these in order.<br><br>1) Add to your MAXIMUM damage. The formula referenced above shows that a higher strength will raise your MAXIMUM damage. However, you will not hit for your maximum every time. If you graph the damage you do on your hits, you will see a large spike in the graph at a point that is twice the damage on the weapon you are using. On an 11 damage weapon, you will see a lot of hits for 21, 22, and 23. You will occasionally see hits higher than this based on your str and weapon skill, but these are offset by the lower hits you'll get. Don't be concerned about hitting for 50 and 60 pts. I'd rather hit 4 times for 22, than once for 30 and 3 times for 10. <br><br>2) Increase your ATK number. A higher str adds to your attack, but if you play around with str items, you will only see a small increase in your ATK number. You WILL see a huge increase in your ATK number AFTER you level AND max out your skill in whatever weapon you are using. For example, at lvl 34 with 99 str, with a 1hb weapon in hand my ATK was around 709. When I hit 35 and maxed my skill in 1hb, my ATK was 744, with str still at 99.<br><br>3) Allow you to carry more. Not very useful for a monk, especially at higher levels. Once you go over your weight cap you begin to lose AC, so being able to carry 110 vs 90 is pretty insignificant to a monk.<br><br>Edited on 4/23 - <br><br>In the paragraph below, I state to focus on HP or stamina gear. I SHOULD have said to focus on AC and HP gear, with stamina following those two. Once your stamina hits 100, then you can even remove that from the equation, unless you are trying to decide between two pieces of equipment that are very close in stats. See Guru Uniero's post below this one for a clarification on this issue.<br><br>End Edit<br><br>My advice would be to focus on straight HP or Stamina gear. Don't worry about what your str is, the additional damage done because of a high str is insignificant beside the damage you will do by being able to last an additional 30 seconds and killing that even con mob before it kills you. I have never focused at all on raising my str, yet it is 14 points over my base stat. I currently wield a 12dmg weapon myself. At 35 with 99 str I see a LOT of 21-27 hits. Every now and then I'll see one in the high 30's. When I was 25 with the same weapon, my str was around 105 due to the equipment I had on. At that level, I also saw a LOT of 21-27 hits. As you can see, str can affect your max damage, but since you don't hit for your max very often you are better off increasing your hp's and stamina then you are str. As you get better equipment, you'll find that str stat going up without trying to make it do so.<br><br>If you want a complete listing and explanation of damage, here's the link:<br><br><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=66" target=_new>http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=66</a><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Apr 23 11:41:13 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Jheran 53 Human Monk<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=310212</a><br>Victorex 33 Wood Elf Ranger<br><br></td></tr>
