	   <tr><td colspan=2>I found that going to the very top of the tents at any one of the gypsie camp and falling off is enough to raise your safe fall well into the 70's and perhaps even farther (last time I tried I raised my SF from 70-75 in a couple minutes at a tent). It might take a little longer but is absolutely the safest for young monks with few hit points to spare. You only need to fall from just slightly higher than an ogre to increase you SF and the very top of these tents does the trick. Even if you fail you will take no more than 1-3 points of damage.<br><br>Once you have your SF up a bit say 15-20 you can try some other areas like hills and ramps. The very best places I have found were the aviak roost (kfc) in SK because it has a great variation in height, and the aviak 3-spawn tower in Lake Rathetear. But in the end it's always best to take the safest area for you so that you reduce down time.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
