<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101933724990322></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101933724990322><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101933724990322>RE: Damage Bonus</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101933724990322#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>589 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Apr 20th 5:14 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>All melee get a damage bonus starting at level 28.&nbsp;&nbsp;It applies only to damage done by your primary hand - whether with weapons or barefisted - or with a two-handed weapon.  The formula for a H2H or 1HB in the primary hand is<br><br>Damage Bonus = (Level - 25)/3 rounded down.<br><br>This is damage added to a successful hit with your primary hand.<br><br>Two-handed weapons get a different damage bonus.  I don't have a formula, but it's at least as good as the one-hander bonus, and at high levels significantly better.  It is also delay-based, with higher delay weapons getting a bigger bonus.<br><br>At higher levels, when you are dual wielding, you will want a fast weapon in your primary hand.  Fast means that you get that damage bonus added more often.  But, this isn't really an issue till your forties.<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

</ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101929617214113></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101929617214113><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101929617214113>RE: Damage Bonus</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101929617214113#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=57570><span id=Guru>Master Niteklaw</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>286 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Apr 20th 5:55 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Monks do get a damage-bonus, as do other melees.<br><br>The formula is: Your level, minus 25, divided by three, rounding down. So you get ONE point at lvl 28, one more at 31, one at 34 etc, etc.<br><br>The bonus is applied to your PRIMARY hand, that is your primary weapon, or ONE of your hands in HtH or to all hits with a two-handed weapon. This is why you see monks looking for a weapon that is as fast as possible for their primary, even if the ratio isn't too good. You get the bonus damage for every primary hit, so fast weapons equal more damage.<br><br>It does NOT in any way affect the damage dealt with your secondary weapon, so around the level you are at now and up, the order of the day is: FAST weapon in the Primary hand, Good Ratio in Secondary.<br>&nbsp;<br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
