	   <tr><td colspan=2>I recently made a new monk and Im curious about practicing various weapon skills. I made the mistake of twinking my monk a little too much with good weapons, and my weapon skills could not keep up with my levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;I got to level 10 rather quickly, any my 2h2 and 1hb were at least 30 points behind max.  <br>So, note to self: don't twink monks until after 10.<br>Anyway, after skipping quest, dumping way too many practice points into weapon skills, Ive got everything caught up at level 12, except 2hb.  While I dont intend to use 2hb a lot, it doesn't hurt to have everything caught up, and there are some really nice monk 2hb's later in the game.  So, at what level is it too late to start practicing a weapon skill?  Do you think that 12 levels of unuse is too many, or will I be ok just starting now?<br><br>Thanks<br>Lunar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
