<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10192339496341></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10192339496341><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=10192339496341>RE: Weapon skills, esp. 2hb</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=10192339496341#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=141592><span id=Scholar>dabrock</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>72 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 19th 12:38 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Another good weapon for 2hb is the bamboo bo stick. It is very light and fast, but doesn't do much damage. The main benefits are that it won't weigh you down or run you out of stamana like many 2hb weapons, and because of it's speed it allows you to swing a lot which means you get your skill up much faster than a slow weapon. If you have a lot of extra skill points to spend you might want to sink about 10 of them into 2hb before you start training it seriously, and doing it in a group or with a partner who knows you are training it will help. You could take on blues with the other person holding the agro, healing you, or whatever the case might be based on their class.<br><br>With a bamboo bo stick and some help you should be able to get your skill up 15-20 points within 2-3 hours depending on down time. But once you get a really good 2hb weapon you will be glad you did. Especially when you are on high level raids you don't want aggro, and a hard-hitting, slow, 2hb weapon will keep aggro off you while doing more damage over time than 2 1hb weapons. <br><br>Remember, when you are fighting with a warrior and cleric you are not going to tank a lot, and if they know what they are doing they don't want you to tank a lot either, because that will mean the cleric needs to heal you more often than a warrior to keep you alive. Grab a good 2hb (like a IFS or Tstaff) and you will keep everyone happy while you inflict massive damage and yet not risk killing yourself and everyone else by pulling agro when you shouldn't.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
