	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are under level 30, or will be fighting a lot of giants, try a admandite bo stick (aka suicide stick). Some 30+ monks swear by the admandite bo stick, most others swear at them and give up when they start procing. You should be able to pick up one cheap since their is little interest in them by those that can afford them.<br><br>I would also look into a fungus covered tarmok staff which I found for 750, but it is probably worth around 1500. It is very ligth at 2.5 stone but it is a little slow at 30/45, but the damage/delay ratio is equal to the admandaite bo sick (1.5). Add in 7 damage for disease and it can be as high a 37/45 weapon if you fight a mob that has low disease resistance and you can deal massive damage.<br><br>Take a look at the equipment list here and search by ratio. You should be able to find a lot of 1.5 - 2.0 ratio 2hb weapons in your given price range. Just try to keep the weight low or you will run out of stamina very quickly, plus you will likely go over your weight limit.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
