	   <tr><td colspan=2>Grab yourself an abandoned orc shovel, off the ground at the orc camp in lake rathe. It is a 2hb, and is 4dmg/27dly. Horrible weapon, but great for raising skill, especially if you have a haste item as well. The easiest thing to do is have a friend mage or necro make a pet thats blue to you, and smack the heck out of it until your skill is maxxed. Otherwise, just fight light blues, or group and only use the shovel when the mobs are well under control.<br><br>You definitely want your 2hb maxxed. Wouldn't it suck to win the roll on a t staff (or better) and not be able to use it, because your skill is too low to hit anything. Best yuo try to raise your skill now, while you can still kill light blues with the orc shovel, than to wait until you are even higher level.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
