<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101839323812190></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101839323812190><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101839323812190>RE: Riposte and Disiplines</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=101839323812190#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35651><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>589 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Apr 9th 7:00 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Riposte is an automatic skill.&nbsp;&nbsp;Whenever a mob swings at you, you have a chance to riposte.  If you successfully riposte, you turn the mob's attack back on it.  Instead of it damaging you, you damage it, and the damage you give is based on what weapon you're swinging.  You've trained it at the guild hall - now don't worry about it - nothing more you need to do.<br><br>Disciplines, on the other hand, are not trained.  They are just there.  When you want to use it, type /disc resistant.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

