	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was reluctant to suggest getting a Goranga Club for one simple reason: If you spam a zone asking for hand-outs, you are generally being very, very annoying. Some people are ok with this, some just block it out, but if you keep pestering everyone, you are ruining the playing fun for others.<br><br>This is the very reason why I do not have a Goranga Club yet. I will be getting one at some time when others in my guild go there, but I will NOT be in maiden's Eye spamming the airways obnixiously.<br><br>If you have a way to quietly notify those present that you would like a club, by all means do so. But some of the things that go on in Maiden's Eye are bordering on harassment, and unless you choose your words carefully, you could very well be petitioned, or at least yelled at very loudly.<br><br>-Moderation in all things. You might get a club by being a pain for 1 hour, or get one by being a nice person in 2 hours. I hope you will choose the latter option, if you decide to go.<br>&nbsp;<br>Niteklaw Ahzi'Dahaka<br>Iksar Monk<br>Povar Tarew Alliance, Xev.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115679</a></td></tr>
