<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=1018321186890></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f1018321186890><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=1018321186890>RE: Taunting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=1018321186890#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=118989><span id=Sage>Superchum</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>72 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Apr 8th 11:04 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Monk tricks for gaining aggro are few and far between ...<br><br>Here are mine:<br><br>1) BEAT THE SNOT OUT OF IT! I notice that a quad gets a mobs attention right quick. Especially when finished off with a BIG Flying Kick.<br><br>2) Disarm. It's sad but true. Disarm can increase hate. But it's not that effective. Heh. Still at least it's SOMETHING.<br><br>3) Instill Doubt. Not to be used ALL the time. But there are some instances where a FEAR spell will work and will buy your crew enough time to deal with the chaos. AND of course, it'll make the mob hate you a bit more.<br><br>4) SIT DOWN. Sitting sometimes helps increase aggro. I've found that when I want to break mez a combo of sitting down and attempting to disarm the mezzed mob helps the mob hate me a bit more.<br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>-Wubao<br>&nbsp;<br>"Mental gives the signal to the physical ... whirlwind kicks and hits from every angle."</td></tr>
